  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Ketamine (an analgesic drug often associated with morphine in the treatment of Opioid Induced
      Hyperalgesia) is often mixed in Morphine PCA syringe. We make the hypothesis that ketamine
      administrated separately via a continuous infusion, could induced a better analgesic effect.

      We will perform a randomised double blind study to determine the best infusion mode of
      intravenous ketamine, associated with morphine in PCA syringe or alone in continuous
      infusion.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Double blind study to determine the best infusion mode of intravenous ketamine, associated
      with morphine in PCA syringe or alone in continuous infusion
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
